  ('prep-math-minimum-moves-to-equal-array-elements::init', 'prep-math-minimum-moves-to-equal-array-elements', 'At the start of a run (Minimum Moves to Equal Array Elements), what strategy is established?', 'Minimum Moves to Equal Array Elements: one move adds 1 to n−1 elements. Adding to everyone-but-one is the same as subtracting 1 from that one element, so the answer is the total number of single decrements needed to pull every element down to the minimum: sum − n·min.', 1),
