  ('prep-math-power-two::init', 'prep-math-power-two', 'At the start of a run (Power two), what strategy is established?', 'Power of Two: a number is a power of two when its binary form has exactly one set bit (like 1, 10, 100…). The trick n > 0 && (n & (n-1)) == 0 tests that in O(1). Start with n = .', 1),
