  ('prep-stacks-queues-basic-calculator::outcome', 'prep-stacks-queues-basic-calculator', 'When the run completes, what does the final step convey?', 'Reached the end of the string. The fully evaluated expression "" = .', 5),
  ('prep-stacks-queues-buildings-with-an-ocean-view::pattern', 'prep-stacks-queues-buildings-with-an-ocean-view', 'Which approach fits "Buildings With an Ocean View"?', 'Scan right-to-left tracking `maxH`; if `heights[i] > maxH`, building `i` has a view', 0),
  ('prep-stacks-queues-buildings-with-an-ocean-view::init', 'prep-stacks-queues-buildings-with-an-ocean-view', 'At the start of a run (Buildings With an Ocean View), what strategy is established?', 'Buildings With an Ocean View: the ocean is to the right. A building sees the ocean only if every building to its right is strictly shorter. Scan right-to-left tracking maxH (the tallest seen so far); any building taller than maxH has a clear view.', 1),
  ('prep-stacks-queues-buildings-with-an-ocean-view::key-step', 'prep-stacks-queues-buildings-with-an-ocean-view', 'On the "VIEW" step (+), what happens?', ' > , so nothing to the right blocks building  — it has an ocean view. Record index  and raise maxH to .', 2),
