  ('prep-stacks-queues-buildings-with-an-ocean-view::complexity', 'prep-stacks-queues-buildings-with-an-ocean-view', 'What are the time and space complexities for "Buildings With an Ocean View"?', 'O(n). O(n). Scan right-to-left tracking `maxH`; if `heights[i] > maxH`, building `i` has a view; Collect indices in reverse, then reverse the result at the end', 4),
  ('prep-stacks-queues-buildings-with-an-ocean-view::outcome', 'prep-stacks-queues-buildings-with-an-ocean-view', 'When the run completes, what does the final step convey?', 'Scan complete. We collected the view-having indices right-to-left, so reverse them into ascending order: []. These are the buildings with an ocean view.', 5),
  ('prep-stacks-queues-calculate-infix::pattern', 'prep-stacks-queues-calculate-infix', 'Which approach fits "Calculate infix"?', 'Two stacks (numbers and ops); flush pending ops by precedence', 0),
  ('prep-stacks-queues-calculate-infix::init', 'prep-stacks-queues-calculate-infix', 'At the start of a run (Calculate infix), what strategy is established?', 'Calculate Infix: evaluate "" with operator precedence using two stacks — one for numbers, one for operators. Time O(n), Space O(n).', 1),
  ('prep-stacks-queues-calculate-infix::key-step', 'prep-stacks-queues-calculate-infix', 'On the "PUSH_OP" step (push ), what happens?', 'No higher- or equal-precedence operator pending, so push '''' onto the operator stack to wait for its right operand.', 2),
  ('prep-stacks-queues-calculate-infix::state', 'prep-stacks-queues-calculate-infix', 'What does the `i` field track in the visualization state?', 'The recorder keeps `i` in sync: index of the char we are looking at', 3),
