  ('prep-stacks-queues-calculate-postfix::pattern', 'prep-stacks-queues-calculate-postfix', 'Which approach fits "Calculate postfix"?', 'Numbers push; an operator pops two and pushes the result', 0),
  ('prep-stacks-queues-calculate-postfix::init', 'prep-stacks-queues-calculate-postfix', 'At the start of a run (Calculate postfix), what strategy is established?', 'Postfix (Reverse Polish) evaluation: scan tokens left to right. A number is pushed onto the stack; an operator pops the top two values, applies the op, and pushes the result. When done, the single remaining value is the answer.', 1),
  ('prep-stacks-queues-calculate-postfix::key-step', 'prep-stacks-queues-calculate-postfix', 'On the "APPLY" step (   = ), what happens?', 'Apply the operator: a  b =    = . Remove both operands and push the result  back onto the stack.', 2),
  ('prep-stacks-queues-calculate-postfix::state', 'prep-stacks-queues-calculate-postfix', 'What does the `ti` field track in the visualization state?', 'The recorder keeps `ti` in sync: index of the token currently being processed', 3),
