  ('prep-stacks-queues-decode-string::pattern', 'prep-stacks-queues-decode-string', 'Which approach fits "Decode String"?', 'Two stacks: one for counts, one for strings built so far', 0),
  ('prep-stacks-queues-decode-string::init', 'prep-stacks-queues-decode-string', 'At the start of a run (Decode String), what strategy is established?', 'Decode String: expand a pattern like k[...] into k copies of the inner string. We use two stacks — one for the repeat counts, one for the strings built so far — plus a running number "num" and the current string "cur".', 1),
  ('prep-stacks-queues-decode-string::key-step', 'prep-stacks-queues-decode-string', 'On the "CHAR" step (cur=""), what happens?', ''''' is a plain letter, so append it to the current string: cur = "".', 2),
