  ('prep-stacks-queues-find-max-in-sliding-window::pattern', 'prep-stacks-queues-find-max-in-sliding-window', 'Which approach fits "Find max in sliding window"?', 'Decreasing deque of indices; the front holds the window max', 0),
  ('prep-stacks-queues-find-max-in-sliding-window::init', 'prep-stacks-queues-find-max-in-sliding-window', 'At the start of a run (Find max in sliding window), what strategy is established?', 'Find the max of every window of size . We keep a deque of indices whose values are strictly decreasing front-to-back, so the front index always holds the current window''s maximum. Time O(n), Space O().', 1),
