  ('prep-stacks-queues-find-moving-average-in-sliding::pattern', 'prep-stacks-queues-find-moving-average-in-sliding', 'Which approach fits "Find moving average in sliding"?', 'Fixed-size window slides; answer is sum/size', 0),
  ('prep-stacks-queues-find-moving-average-in-sliding::init', 'prep-stacks-queues-find-moving-average-in-sliding', 'At the start of a run (Find moving average in sliding), what strategy is established?', 'Moving Average: keep a queue holding at most k= of the most recent values plus their running sum. Each Next(v) appends v and adds it to the sum, evicts the oldest if the window overflows, then returns sum ÷ window length — all in O(1).', 1),
