  ('prep-stacks-queues-infix-to-postfix::pattern', 'prep-stacks-queues-infix-to-postfix', 'Which approach fits "Infix to postfix"?', 'Operands flow straight to output; operators wait on a precedence stack', 0),
  ('prep-stacks-queues-infix-to-postfix::init', 'prep-stacks-queues-infix-to-postfix', 'At the start of a run (Infix to postfix), what strategy is established?', 'Infix → postfix via the shunting-yard scan (no parentheses). Operands flow straight to the output; operators wait on a precedence stack. Rule: before pushing operator c, pop every stacked operator whose precedence is ≥ prec(c).', 1),
